{
  "stem": "19550.8",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 220.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There would be children or women would stand along the street and throw us some food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Or children would run into the line, and before they were caught, and stick a piece of bread or something into our hands.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we would go through, incidentally, this is, sounds like a heartwarming kind of story.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The more important aspect of it is that this has happened in my Germany, that is, that we were being marched through the cities and the states-- I mean, and the villages.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And aside from all other facts of life, the German claim that they didn't know is, on the face of it, so false.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean as I have once said to, many years ago, to a German in Frankfurt, you didn't see me, but I saw you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And you can't tell me that you don't know about me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because we were marched through the cities, and villages, and towns.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All they, all they had to see, the condition that we were in, and the manner in which we were being treated, even just as we were being driven to work or back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was enough for anyone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, you know, the brutality with which we were driven in and out of camp was absolutely enough for anybody.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, the butts of the carbines, or whatever the heck they were carrying, and the shouting, and the dogs around us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if somebody fell, they would right away start tearing us all apart, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was no way in which any civilian German, even if he did not live in a, in a town or a city where we were being driven across, but it's enough if you are driven across one town.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
